§ CSLv3-AS-SURFACE QUESTION  ← §§ S10.5 ★ core-decision
  Q? W! CSSLv3-surface-syntax = CSLv3-notation ?
    OR W! CSSLv3-surface = more-conventional ?
  
  § case-for CSLv3-as-surface :
    ✓ already-designed • already-readable-by-Apocky-and-Claude
    ✓ density = 5-6× English (if claims-hold)
    ✓ trilingual : EN-bridge + compounds + ASCII-aliases
    ✓ § think-blocks → useful-for-code-annotations (stage-markers)
    ✓ self-consistent : spec-lang ≡ prog-lang (one-language)
  § case-against :
    ✗ too-novel : new-contributors face wall
    ✗ tooling-starved : no-LSP no-editor-support
    ✗ domain-overlap : spec-glyphs (I> W! ∎) don't map-to prog-concepts cleanly
    ✗ CSLv3 lacks expressions rich-enough for full-lang
      e.g. arithmetic-ops • control-flow-expr-form • pattern-match

  § hybrid OPTION : CSLv3-as-CoT + CSSLv3-as-surface
    CSLv3 → § think-blocks • CoT • comments • spec-docs
    CSSLv3 → fn body + type-defs + expressions
    ≡ "CSLv3 inside /* ... */ block + CSSLv3 outside"
    ≡ literate-programming pattern
    ‼ tentative-preferred

  § CSSLv3-surface TENTATIVE (example)
    ```
    § CSL-thinking-allowed in comments
    § ✓ CSSLv3-primary-syntax below

    @differentiable
    @lipschitz(1.0)
    fn sphere_sdf(p : vec3, r : f32'pos) -> f32 =
      length(p) - r

    @staged
    fn render_scene<scene : Scene>(
      cam : Camera
    ) -> Image / {GPU, Deadline<16ms>, NoAlloc} {
      for (x, y) in grid(cam.size) |> parallel {
        ray := cam.ray(x, y)
        hit := ray_march(scene, ray) ?: return background
        n   := bwd_diff(sdf)(hit.pos)      § ← F1 compiler-inserts
        emit pixel(x, y, shade(hit, n))
      }
    }

    effect Physics<World> {
      step       : dt : f32 -> World
      contact    : a : Entity, b : Entity -> Option<Hit>
    }
    ```

  § SYNTAX-DECISIONS (tentative)
    type-annotation : x : T
    refinement : x : T'tag OR x : T{P(x)}
    effect-row : / {E1, E2<N>, ...}
    attribute : @name(args)
    staging : @staged fn ...   § ← staged in F4
    pattern-match : match x { Some(v) => ..., None => ... }
    lambda : |x : T| -> U { body }  or  \x. body
    arrow : → for type-sig • =>  for match-arm
    generics : fn f<T : Trait>(...) ...

